The prerequisite to this course is the completed "Introduction to Design" course, for Tartu students the theoretical introduction is being made in the beginning of the course.
Prior to practical project the analysis of purposes and assumptions of problems, and material assessment is applied, based on the principles and methods of strategic and sustainable design. Different approaches of product-service systems, circular and collaborative design are applied. The project includes the research of connections between cultural heritage and contemporary design, how to implement different approaches and use them in practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to support a creative person's ability to analyse and develop products and services according to her/his field and focus, based on the principles and methods of strategic and sustainable design. A practical project is at the core of the course.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the students should - has the ability to create connections between the heritage and historical continuity of the material culture and contemporary design within one's self reflection and work; ­ has the knowledge and skills to implement the principles and methods of strategic and sustainable design; ­ can implement the integrated process of product-service systems design, circular and collaborative design; - can analyse the meanings and values in the context of designing products and services; - has developed good analytical skills and systemic thinking competencies.
